      "Text": "ImageMagick security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ImageMagick is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Use ImageMagick to create, edit, compose, or convert bitmap images. It can read and write images in a variety of formats (over 200) including PNG, JPEG, GIF, HEIC, TIFF, DPX, EXR, WebP, Postscript, PDF, and SVG. Use ImageMagick to resize, flip, mirror, rotate, distort, shear and transform images, adjust image colors, apply various special effects, or draw text, lines, polygons, ellipses and BÃ©zier curves.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nImageMagick contains an integer overflow vulnerability in the BMP decoder. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by providing a specially crafted BMP file, leading to buffer overflow or denial of service.(CVE-2025-62171)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ImageMagick is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "ImageMagick",
